title: Programmed College Vocabulary 3600 (1979)
description:
Programmed College Vocabulary 3600 2nd. ed. (1979)


Description:

George Feinstein's Programmed College Vocabulary, prepares students for college course work by covering literary and academic terms. Stressing the basic terminology of fiction, poetry, psychology, and social science, this self-paced text is grounded in the belief that students can learn anything that is broken down into easy steps.


Notes:

1. 270 pages

2. About 20-25 of the beginning pages contain markings.

3. A few pages are missing: end of section review.
